Entries.default: Your crew hauls the crates aboard, stepping carefully around the bodies.
Once you've caught the wind, you turn to Iverra, who is watching the waters below your ship with pleasure and fascination.
The smugglers unload the crates onto your ship.
They also haul a few other boxes out of the hold - the supplies Widla promised you.
Your new cargo secured, you retract the anchor and let out your sails.
Several crates, now bloodstained, are stacked together.
